  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dd0\u0dba 3\u0d9a \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0db4\u0dca\u0db4\u0dcf\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0dad\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0daf\u0dd2\u0db1 7\u0d9a\u0da7 \u0daf\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The 3-hour power cut will be extended for another 7 days",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Janaka Ratnayake, chairman of the Public Utilities Commission, said this afternoon (8) that due to the lack of sufficient fuel and water for power generation, the current 3-hour power cut was allowed to be extended tomorrow (9) until the 15th of this month.",
        "Accordingly, Mr. Ratnayake said that electricity will be cut for 3 hours for the next seven days and 20 zones from 'A' to 'W' will be cut for 1 hour and 40 minutes during the day and 20 hours and 20 minutes at night.",
        "6.00 am to 8.30 am for 'CC' category which includes Colombo cities and 2 hours and 30 minutes (except on 9th, 10th and 13th), for M, N, O, X, Y and Z zones from 5.30 am to 8.30 am. Janaka Ratnayake, chairman of the Public Utilities Commission, further said that power cuts were allowed for 3 hours (except on the 9th, 10th and 13th)."
      ],
